        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">Understanding Google Rankings</h2>
        <p>
          Google's ranking algorithm considers numerous factors when ranking websites. These include website content, backlinks,
          mobile-friendliness, and page speed. Understanding these elements is crucial for improving your site's visibility.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">1. Create Quality Content</h2>
        <p>
          Content is the foundation of your website’s success. Write original, informative, and engaging material tailored to your
          target audience. Address their pain points, answer their questions, and provide value they can’t find elsewhere. Consider
          creating guides, directories, or other helpful content that will attract traffic for years to come.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">2. Use Relevant Keywords Strategically</h2>
        <p>
          Keywords help search engines understand your content. Research terms your audience searches for using tools like Google
          Keyword Planner, and incorporate them naturally into titles and headings, meta descriptions, alt-text for images, and your
          website's body text.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">3. Mention Your Business “ABCs”</h2>
        <p>
          Make sure your website includes essential business details including your address, phone number, and business email. This
          builds trust and improves local search visibility.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">4. Optimize and Link Your Google Business Profile</h2>
        <p>
          Claim and complete your Google Business Profile to improve your local search presence. Optimize it by adding your address,
          phone number, and website, uploading high-quality photos, and collecting and responding to reviews.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">5. Build Backlinks</h2>
        <p>
          Backlinks from reputable websites signal to Google that your site is trustworthy. Earn backlinks by writing guest posts,
          sharing your content on social media, and networking with local businesses or influencers.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">6. Improve Your On-Page SEO</h2>
        <p>
          Focus on descriptive, keyword-rich titles and meta descriptions, structure content with clear headings (H1, H2, H3), and add
          internal links to guide visitors.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">7. Leverage Local SEO</h2>
        <p>
          If you serve a specific area, use location-specific keywords, list your business in local directories, and encourage
          reviews.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">8. Regularly Update and Refresh Content</h2>
        <p>
          Keep your website fresh by updating outdated information, adding new posts or pages, and revisiting old content to improve
          keywords, links, and readability.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">9. Add Engaging Visuals</h2>
        <p>
          Use images, videos, and infographics to boost engagement. Optimize assets and include descriptive alt text.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">10. Monitor and Adjust with Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Track performance in Google Analytics and Search Console (organic traffic, bounce rate, keyword rankings) and refine your
          approach over time.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading-font" style="color:var(--ink);font-size:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
          Improving your Google rankings doesn’t have to be complicated. Focus on these steps to drive more traffic, connect with your
          audience, and grow your business—no expert required.
        </p>
